<item>
            <title>[SOLR-7800] avg() facet function counts missing values</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-7800</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The avg() facet function currently counts missing values as 0 (so the average of &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;3,3,missing&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; is currently 2 instead of 3.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We should change it so that missing values are entirely skipped.&lt;br/&gt;
If 0 values are desired for missing values, that can be expressed using the &quot;def&quot; function query:  avg(def(myfield,0))&lt;/p&gt;</description>
